idge-to-zfs.owl`\n  - Life-stage bridge artifact (`ZFS` zebrafish stages).\n\nMixed / caution: not purely life-stage bridge artifacts, but contain life-stage `BFO_0000066` axioms\n- `/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/bridge/uberon-bridge-to-xao.owl`\n  - Mixed bridge. Mostly anatomy/XAO bridge, but includes Xenopus life-stage axioms using `BFO_0000066` near the `XAO:1000000` developmental-stage block and at least one other stage term (`death stage`).\n- `/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/bridge/uberon-bridge-to-fma.owl`\n  - Mixed bridge. Primarily FMA anatomy bridge, but contains a small number of human life-stage/developmental-stage axioms using `BFO_0000066`.\n\nNon-OWL generator/rule files that also contain `BFO:0000066`\n- `/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/bridge/bridge-xao-ls.rules`\n  - Explicit special life-stage bridge rules for XAO; likely directly relevant to issue #3409.\n- `/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/bridge/bridges.rules`\n  - Generic bridge-generation rules; explicitly says life-stage terms use `occurs_in (BFO:0000066)` instead of `part_of`.\n\nCautionary notes\n- Not every hit is a life-stage artifact file: `uberon-bridge-to-fma.owl` and `uberon-bridge-to-xao.owl` are mixed-content bridges and should be reviewed carefully, not blanket-updated as if they were pure life-stage outputs.\n- Some matches are only declarations/comments/templates, not asserted bridge axioms:\n  - object property declarations at file headers\n  - rule templates in `bridges.rules` and `bridge-xao-ls.rules`\n- I did not find other non-life-stage `.owl` bridge files under `src/ontology/bridge` containing `BFO_0000066` beyond:\n  - `/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/bridge/uberon-bridge-to-fma.owl`\n  - `/__w/eval-ont-agent-uberon/eval-ont-agent-uberon/src/ontology/bridge/uberon-bridge-to-xao.owl`\n</task_result>","metadata":{"parentSe